### Dermoscanners API Testing
### Use with REST Client extension in VS Code or Thunder Client

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5001
@token = YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### ============================================
### HEALTH CHECK
### ============================================

GET {{baseUrl}}/api/health

### ============================================
### PRODUCT ENDPOINTS
### ============================================

### Get Product by Barcode
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products/barcode/3700123456789

### Search Products
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products/search?q=cerave

### List All Products
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products

### List Products with Filters
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products?category=cleanser&skinType=oily

### List Products Sorted by Price
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products?sortBy=price

### Get Recommendations
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products/recommendations?skinType=oily&maxPrice=20

### Get Product by ID (replace with actual ID)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products/PRODUCT_ID_HERE

### ============================================
### AUTH ENDPOINTS
### ============================================

### Register New User
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "Test123456",
  "skinType": "oily",
  "skinGoals": "Reduce oiliness and prevent breakouts"
}

### Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "Test123456"
}

### ============================================
### SCAN HISTORY ENDPOINTS (Protected)
### ============================================

### Add to History
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/history
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productId": "PRODUCT_ID_HERE"
}

### Get History
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/history
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Delete History Entry
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/history/ENTRY_ID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Clear All History
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/history
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ============================================
### INGREDIENT SAFETY ENDPOINTS
### ============================================

### Analyze Single Ingredient
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/ingredients/analyze
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ingredient": "Retinol"
}

### Analyze Product Ingredients
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/ingredients/analyze-product
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ingredients": ["Retinol", "Hyaluronic Acid", "Niacinamide", "Sodium Lauryl Sulfate"]
}

### Check Skin Type Compatibility
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/ingredients/check-compatibility
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ingredient": "Retinol",
  "skinType": "sensitive"
}

### Get Ingredient Info
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/ingredients/info/Hyaluronic%20Acid

### Batch Analyze Ingredients
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/ingredients/batch-analyze
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ingredients": ["Retinol", "Hyaluronic Acid", "Niacinamide", "Ceramides", "Glycerin"]
}

### ============================================
### RECOMMENDATION ENDPOINTS
### ============================================

### Get Personalized Recommendations
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/recommendations?skinType=oily&maxPrice=30

### Get Similar Products
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/recommendations/similar/PRODUCT_ID_HERE

### Get Trending Products
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/recommendations/trending

### Get Safe Alternatives
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/recommendations/alternatives/PRODUCT_ID_HERE

### Get Budget Recommendations
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/recommendations/budget?skinType=oily&maxPrice=20

### ============================================
### SENTIMENT ANALYSIS ENDPOINTS
### ============================================

### Analyze Sentiment
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sentiment/analyze
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "I love this product! It works great and my skin feels amazing!"
}

### Analyze Negative Sentiment
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sentiment/analyze
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "This product is terrible. It caused irritation and redness."
}

### Analyze Multiple Reviews
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sentiment/analyze-reviews
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reviews": [
    { "comment": "Great product! Love it!" },
    { "comment": "Works well, very gentle" },
    { "comment": "Not bad, but could be better" },
    { "comment": "Terrible, caused breakouts" }
  ]
}

